///
Module: sdn

SDN (Simple Data Notation) parser and serializer library.

A minimal, token-efficient data notation format optimized for:
- LLM context windows
- Human readability
- One-pass parsing (LL(2) max lookahead)
- Embeddability in Simple source code

Usage:
    use sdn

    # Parse SDN from string
    val doc = sdn.parse("name: Alice\nage: 30")

    # Access values
    val name = doc.get("name").as_str()  # Some("Alice")
    val age = doc.get("age").as_i64()    # Some(30)

    # Path navigation
    val port = doc.get_path("server.port")

Components:
- error: Error types and span tracking
- token: Token definitions
- value: Value representation
- lexer: Tokenization with INDENT/DEDENT
- parser: LL(2) recursive descent parser
- document: Editable document API
- serializer: SDN output formatter
